(830, '_transient_ao3_ccss_explain', '<div class=\'ao_i18n\' id=\'default\'>\n    <h2>Improve performance with critical CSS</h2>\n    <div style=\"width:100%;overflow:hidden\">\n    <div style=\"width:68%;float:left\">\n      <p>Autoptimize\'s Critical CSS speeds up your site by improving Google PageSpeed Insights performance indicators like <strong>\"first contentful paint\"</strong> and \"largest contentful paint\". Having the <strong>correct rules for each page</strong> is key to avoid \"cumulative layout shift\".</p>\n      <p><strong><a href=\"https://autoptimize.com/pro/\" target=\"_blank\">Autoptimize Pro</a> fully automates critical CSS rule creation</strong>, but also provides image optimization, CDN and extra powerful \"booster\" options all in one handy subscription to make your site even faster! See <a href=\"https://autoptimize.com/pro/\" target=\"_blank\">https://autoptimize.com/pro/</a> for more info and maybe a discount code?</p>\n      <p>Alternatively with <a href=\"https://criticalcss.com/?aff=1\" target=\"_blank\">criticalcss.com\'s 3EUR (4USD)/  month subscription</a> you can generate the right critical CSS for any given page and create manual rules yourself. You can also <strong>automate the entire process</strong> by opting for the \"WordPress\" plan (3EUR or 4USD subscription + 8EUR or 10USD per domain); simply <a href=\"https://criticalcss.com/?aff=1\" target=\"_blank\">sign up</a>, copy/ paste <a href=\"https://criticalcss.com/account/api-keys?aff=1\" target=\"_blank\">the API key</a> in the field below and Autoptimize will automatically start creating rules!</p>\n      <p>If you have any questions or need support, head on over to <a href=\"https://wordpress.org/support/plugin/autoptimize\" target=\"_blank\">our support forum</a> and we\'ll help you get up and running in no time!</p>\n    </div>\n    <div style=\"width:28%;float:right\"><img src=\"https://criticalcss.com/images/criticalcss-optimised-website-illustration.svg\" width=\"350px\